text: Maol Choluim II, anglicised to Malcolm II (d. 1266) was one of the people involved in the famous coronation of Alexander III in 1249, he reigned as Earl of Fife from 1228 until 1266. == References == Category:Scottish Earls Category:1200s births Category:1266 deaths
title: Maol Choluim II, Earl of Fife
